        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 2:56PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 255 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Westville, or 10 miles north of Lake Wateree Dam, moving east at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kershaw, Heath Springs, Westville, Mt Pisgah, Kershaw Correctional
Institution, North Central High School, and Lake Wateree near Highway
97.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
